Massoni</a></div><div class="_f4aa7e38"><div class="_e9c83e5b"><h2 data-tn="pdp-storytelling-creator-name" class="_54e1e428">Luigi Massoni</h2></div><div class="_f03247da"><p><a target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" href="/creators/luigi-massoni/furniture/" tabindex="-1">Luigi Massoni</a> was one of Italy’s most prolific designers and instrumental in the growth of the country’s design industry in the postwar years through his products, advertising campaigns and journalistic work at Italian magazines.</p><p>Born in Milan, Massoni trained at the Collettivo di Architettura in Milan and worked as an architect and designer as well as a freelance journalist and consultant. He was involved with many of Italy’s most influential brands, such as <a target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" href="/creators/poltrona-frau/furniture/" tabindex="-1">Poltrona Frau</a>, the <a target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" href="/creators/guzzini/furniture/" tabindex="-1">Guzzini</a> group and <a target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" href="/creators/alessi/furniture/" tabindex="-1">Alessi</a>. Massoni was hired by Alessi, the legendary housewares and kitchen utensils manufacturer, which had been around since 1921, in the mid-1950s. In 1957, he collaborated with like-minded product designer Carlo Mazzeri on the universally renowned <a target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" href="https://www.moma.org/collection/works/4678" tabindex="-1">stainless-steel cocktail shaker 870</a>, which, followed by other kitchen containers for the brand, was one of the first objects from Alessi that hadn’t been created in-house.</p><p>Together with architect <a target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" href="/creators/carlo-de-carli/furniture/" tabindex="-1">Carlo De Carli</a>, Massoni founded a magazine called <em>Il Mobile Italiano</em> and later Mobilia, an association of Italian furniture makers and one of the first organizations that focused on the promotion of Italian design. In the 1960s, Massoni began to design lamps and serveware for Guzzini, where he also consulted on design and company communications. He designed revolutionary furnishings for the kitchen at Boffi Cucine, producing modular kitchens, cabinets without traditional handles and more.</p><p>On 1stDibs, browse a collection of <a target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" href="/buy/luigi-massoni-vanity/" tabindex="-1">vintage Luigi Massoni vanity tables</a>, <a target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" href="/creators/luigi-massoni/furniture/storage-case-pieces/sideboards/" tabindex="-1">sideboards</a>, <a target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" href="/creators/luigi-massoni/furniture/lighting/table-lamps/" tabindex="-1">table lamps</a> and more.</p></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="_6c97a9ff" hidden="" role="tabpanel" data-tn="tab-panel-maker-1" aria-labelledby=":Rdaja:" id=":R3ija:"><div><div class="_e453eff5 _592abbf9" data-tn="maker-1-tab-content"><div class="_af720ab"><div class="_d6a95974 _6de5265d"><div class="_80ad38ae"><img class="_178b37dd" src="https://a.1stdibscdn.com/italian-mid-century-chrome-ribbon-wall-sconces-by-harvey-guzzini-for-iguzzini-for-sale/f_9224/f_446747121745255548689/f_44674712_1745255549049_bg_processed.jpg?width=520" srcset="https://a.1stdibscdn.com/italian-mid-century-chrome-ribbon-wall-sconces-by-harvey-guzzini-for-iguzzini-for-sale/f_9224/f_446747121745255548689/f_44674712_1745255549049_bg_processed.jpg?width=200&amp;disable=upscale&amp;auto=webp&amp;quality=60 200w, https://a.1stdibscdn.com/italian-mid-century-chrome-ribbon-wall-sconces-by-harvey-guzzini-for-iguzzini-for-sale/f_9224/f_446747121745255548689/f_44674712_1745255549049_bg_processed.jpg?width=320&amp;disable=upscale&amp;auto=webp&amp;quality=60 320w, https://a.1stdibscdn.com/italian-mid-century-chrome-ribbon-wall-sconces-by-harvey-guzzini-for-iguzzini-for-sale/f_9224/f_446747121745255548689/f_44674712_1745255549049_bg_processed.jpg?width=400&amp;disable=upscale&amp;auto=webp&amp;quality=60 400w, https://a.1stdibscdn.com/italian-mid-century-chrome-ribbon-wall-sconces-by-harvey-guzzini-for-iguzzini-for-sale/f_9224/f_446747121745255548689/f_44674712_1745255549049_bg_processed.jpg?width=640&amp;disable=upscale&amp;auto=webp&amp;quality=60 640w, https://a.1stdibscdn.com/italian-mid-century-chrome-ribbon-wall-sconces-by-harvey-guzzini-for-iguzzini-for-sale/f_9224/f_446747121745255548689/f_44674712_1745255549049_bg_processed.jpg?width=800&amp;disable=upscale&amp;auto=webp&amp;quality=60 800w, https://a.1stdibscdn.com/italian-mid-century-chrome-ribbon-wall-sconces-by-harvey-guzzini-for-iguzzini-for-sale/f_9224/f_446747121745255548689/f_44674712_1745255549049_bg_processed.jpg?width=960&amp;disable=upscale&amp;auto=webp&amp;quality=60 960w" sizes="20vw" alt=""></div><a href="/creators/harvey-guzzini/" data-tn="pdp-storytelling-shop-all-link" class="" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" tabindex="-1">Shop All Harvey Guzzini</a></div><div class="_f4aa7e38"><div class="_e9c83e5b"><h2 data-tn="pdp-storytelling-creator-name" class="_54e1e428">Harvey Guzzini</h2></div><div class="_f03247da"><p><a target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" href="https://www.1stdibs.com/creators/harvey-guzzini/furniture/" tabindex="-1">Harvey Guzzini</a> may sound like a single designer, but it was actually a <a target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" href="https://www.1stdibs.com/furniture/style/mid-century-modern/" tabindex="-1">mid-century</a> Italian lighting company started by six brothers in the Guzzini family: Giovanni, Raimondo, Giuseppe, Adolfo, Virgilio and Giannunzio. The first part of the name was an homage to the 1950 film <em>Harvey</em>. Compounding the historical record even further, it seems that the Guzzini company rebranded many times in the 20th century, going by, at various points, Harvey Creazioni, <a target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" href="https://www.1stdibs.com/creators/guzzini/furniture/" tabindex="-1">Guzzini</a>, Illuminazione Guzzini and <a target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" href="https://www.1stdibs.com/creators/iguzzini/furniture/" tabindex="-1">iGuzzini</a>.&nbsp;</p>
<p>The Harvey Guzzini brand produced a range of fixtures during the postwar years, including <a target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" href="https://www.1stdibs.com/creators/harvey-guzzini/furniture/lighting/table-lamps/" tabindex="-1">table lamps</a>, <a target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" href="https://www.1stdibs.com/creators/harvey-guzzini/furniture/lighting/floor-lamps/" tabindex="-1">floor lamps</a> and <a target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" href="https://www.1stdibs.com/creators/harvey-guzzini/furniture/lighting/chandeliers-pendant-lights/" tabindex="-1">pendant lights</a>.&nbsp;</p>
<p>Harvey Guzzini was founded in 1959 in a room of Giovanni's home in the town of Recanati. Initially, the company was focused on making copper decorative objects. The brothers quickly established their own studio space and, in 1963, they expanded into lighting production. The following year, they hired prolific Italian designer <a target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" href="https://www.1stdibs.com/creators/luigi-massoni/furniture/" tabindex="-1">Luigi Massoni</a> as head of design. In addition to Harvey Guzzini, Massoni was involved with many of Italy’s most influential brands, such as <a target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" href="https://www.1stdibs.com/creators/poltrona-frau/furniture/" tabindex="-1">Poltrona Frau</a> and <a target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" href="https://www.1stdibs.com/creators/alessi/furniture/" tabindex="-1">Alessi</a>.&nbsp;</p>
<p>Another key to the growing success of Harvey Guzzini was partnerships with a number of Italy's most prominent designers, including <a target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" href="https://www.1stdibs.com/creators/gio-ponti/furniture/" tabindex="-1">Gio Ponti</a>, <a target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" href="https://www.1stdibs.com/creators/fabio-lenci/furniture/" tabindex="-1">Fabio Lenci</a>, <a target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" href="https://www.1stdibs.com/creators/rodolfo-bonetto/furniture/" tabindex="-1">Rodolfo Bonetto</a>, <a target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" href="https://www.1stdibs.com/creators/cesare-casati/furniture/" tabindex="-1">Cesare Casati</a> and <a target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" href="https://www.1stdibs.com/creators/ennio-lucini/furniture/" tabindex="-1">Ennio Lucini</a>.</p>
<p>From 1967 to 1968, Harvey Guzzini also participated in “Domus: Formes Italiennes,” an exhibition held at the <a target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" href="https://haussmann.galerieslafayette.com/en/galeries-lafayette-the-best-shopping-mall-in-paris/" tabindex="-1">Galeries Lafayette</a> in Paris. By 1969, the company had grown into one of the best-known design firms in the country and opened a retail outlet in central Milan. Famous Harvey Guzzini designs include Massoni and Luciano Buttura's <a target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" href="https://www.1stdibs.com/buy/guzzini-mushroom-lamp/" tabindex="-1">Mushroom table lamp</a> (1965) as well as the in-house designed <a target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" href="https://www.1stdibs.com/buy/guzzini-arc-floor-lamp/" tabindex="-1">Arc floor lamp</a> (1968), <a target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" href="https://www.1stdibs.com/buy/guzzini-faro/" tabindex="-1">Faro table lamp</a> (1970) and Toledo table lamp (1973).&nbsp;</p>
<p>In 1974, Harvey Guzzini rebranded as iGuzzini. The company introduced a range of new and technically advanced lighting fixtures, including low-voltage halogen lamps. In 1977, iGuzzini organized the first Italian lighting design conference. In 1991, it was awarded the <a target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" href="https://www.adidesignmuseum.org/en/il-premio-compasso-doro/" tabindex="-1">Compasso d'Oro</a> for its commitment to design.</p>
<p>Today, iGuzzini remains headquartered in Recanati and is a leading international architectural lighting group with a rich heritage spanning more than six decades since its early days as Harvey Guzzini. The company creates lighting fixtures for workplaces, city infrastructure and even cultural heritage sites.</p>
<p>On 1stDibs, find a collection of vintage Harvey Guzzini table lamps, floor lamps and other lighting.</p></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="_6c97a9ff" hidden="" role="tabpanel" Massoni","contentCreatorAttribution":null,"contentBodyText":"\u003cp\u003E\u003ca target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" href=\"/creators/luigi-massoni/furniture/\"\u003ELuigi Massoni\u003c/a\u003E was one of Italy’s most prolific designers and instrumental in the growth of the country’s design industry in the postwar years through his products, advertising campaigns and journalistic work at Italian magazines.\u003c/p\u003E\u003cp\u003EBorn in Milan, Massoni trained at the Collettivo di Architettura in Milan and worked as an architect and designer as well as a freelance journalist and consultant. He was involved with many of Italy’s most influential brands, such as \u003ca target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" href=\"/creators/poltrona-frau/furniture/\"\u003EPoltrona Frau\u003c/a\u003E, the \u003ca target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" href=\"/creators/guzzini/furniture/\"\u003EGuzzini\u003c/a\u003E group and \u003ca target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" href=\"/creators/alessi/furniture/\"\u003EAlessi\u003c/a\u003E. Massoni was hired by Alessi, the legendary housewares and kitchen utensils manufacturer, which had been around since 1921, in the mid-1950s. In 1957, he collaborated with like-minded product designer Carlo Mazzeri on the universally renowned \u003ca target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" href=\"https://www.moma.org/collection/works/4678\"\u003Estainless-steel cocktail shaker 870\u003c/a\u003E, which, followed by other kitchen containers for the brand, was one of the first objects from Alessi that hadn’t been created in-house.\u003c/p\u003E\u003cp\u003ETogether with architect \u003ca target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" href=\"/creators/carlo-de-carli/furniture/\"\u003ECarlo De Carli\u003c/a\u003E, Massoni founded a magazine called \u003cem\u003EIl Mobile Italiano\u003c/em\u003E and later Mobilia, an association of Italian furniture makers and one of the first organizations that focused on the promotion of Italian design. In the 1960s, Massoni began to design lamps and serveware for Guzzini, where he also consulted on design and company communications. He designed revolutionary furnishings for the kitchen at Boffi Cucine, producing modular kitchens, cabinets without traditional handles and more.\u003c/p\u003E\u003cp\u003EOn 1stDibs, browse a collection of \u003ca target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" href=\"/buy/luigi-massoni-vanity/\"\u003Evintage Luigi Massoni vanity tables\u003c/a\u003E, \u003ca target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" href=\"/creators/luigi-massoni/furniture/storage-case-pieces/sideboards/\"\u003Esideboards\u003c/a\u003E, \u003ca target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" href=\"/creators/luigi-massoni/furniture/lighting/table-lamps/\"\u003Etable lamps\u003c/a\u003E and more.\u003c/p\u003E","mainImage":null,"mainVideo":null,"browseLink":{"__ref":"client:SXRlbTpmXzQ1MjI3Mjky:storyTellingModule(shortTitles:true):tabs:0:browseLink"},"smallImage":"https://a.1stdibscdn.com/mid-century-space-age-italian-green-early-model-toledo-table-lamp-1960s-for-sale/56838232/f_440027621742216862499/f_44002762_01_master.jpg?width=520"},"client:SXRlbTpmXzQ1MjI3Mjky:storyTellingModule(shortTitles:true):tabs:0:supplementaryEditorial":{"__id":"client:SXRlbTpmXzQ1MjI3Mjky:storyTellingModule(shortTitles:true):tabs:0:supplementaryEditorial","__typename":"WordpressArticlesType","articles":{"__refs":[]}},"client:SXRlbTpmXzQ1MjI3Mjky:storyTellingModule(shortTitles:true):tabs:1":{"__id":"client:SXRlbTpmXzQ1MjI3Mjky:storyTellingModule(shortTitles:true):tabs:1","__typename":"StoryTellingTab","supplementaryEditorial":{"__ref":"client:SXRlbTpmXzQ1MjI3Mjky:storyTellingModule(shortTitles:true):tabs:1:supplementaryEditorial"},"tabType":"creator","tabTitle":"Maker","contentHeader":"Harvey Guzzini","contentCreatorAttribution":null,"contentBodyText":"\u003cp\u003E\u003ca target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" href=\"https://www.1stdibs.com/creators/harvey-guzzini/furniture/\"\u003EHarvey Guzzini\u003c/a\u003E may sound like a single designer, but it was actually a \u003ca target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" href=\"https://www.1stdibs.com/furniture/style/mid-century-modern/\"\u003Emid-century\u003c/a\u003E Italian lighting company started by six brothers in the Guzzini family: Giovanni, Raimondo, Giuseppe, Adolfo, Virgilio and Giannunzio. The first part of the name was an homage to the 1950 film \u003cem\u003EHarvey\u003c/em\u003E. Compounding the historical record even further, it seems that the Guzzini company rebranded many times in the 20th century, going by, at various points, Harvey Creazioni, \u003ca target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" href=\"https://www.1stdibs.com/creators/guzzini/furniture/\"\u003EGuzzini\u003c/a\u003E, Illuminazione Guzzini and \u003ca target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" href=\"https://www.1stdibs.com/creators/iguzzini/furniture/\"\u003EiGuzzini\u003c/a\u003E.&nbsp;\u003c/p\u003E\n\u003cp\u003EThe Harvey Guzzini brand produced a range of fixtures during the postwar years, including \u003ca target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" href=\"https://www.1stdibs.com/creators/harvey-guzzini/furniture/lighting/table-lamps/\"\u003Etable lamps\u003c/a\u003E, \u003ca target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" href=\"https://www.1stdibs.com/creators/harvey-guzzini/furniture/lighting/floor-lamps/\"\u003Efloor lamps\u003c/a\u003E and \u003ca target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" href=\"https://www.1stdibs.com/creators/harvey-guzzini/furniture/lighting/chandeliers-pendant-lights/\"\u003Ependant lights\u003c/a\u003E.&nbsp;\u003c/p\u003E\n\u003cp\u003EHarvey Guzzini was founded in 1959 in a room of Giovanni's home in the town of Recanati. Initially, the company was focused on making copper decorative objects. The brothers quickly established their own studio space and, in 1963, they expanded into lighting production. The following year, they hired prolific Italian designer \u003ca target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" href=\"https://www.1stdibs.com/creators/luigi-massoni/furniture/\"\u003ELuigi Massoni\u003c/a\u003E as head of design. In addition to Harvey Guzzini, Massoni was involved with many of Italy’s most influential brands, such as \u003ca target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" href=\"https://www.1stdibs.com/creators/poltrona-frau/furniture/\"\u003EPoltrona Frau\u003c/a\u003E and \u003ca target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" href=\"https://www.1stdibs.com/creators/alessi/furniture/\"\u003EAlessi\u003c/a\u003E.&nbsp;\u003c/p\u003E\n\u003cp\u003EAnother key to the growing success of Harvey Guzzini was partnerships with a number of Italy's most prominent designers, including \u003ca target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" href=\"https://www.1stdibs.com/creators/gio-ponti/furniture/\"\u003EGio Ponti\u003c/a\u003E, \u003ca target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" href=\"https://www.1stdibs.com/creators/fabio-lenci/furniture/\"\u003EFabio Lenci\u003c/a\u003E, \u003ca target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" href=\"https://www.1stdibs.com/creators/rodolfo-bonetto/furniture/\"\u003ERodolfo Bonetto\u003c/a\u003E, \u003ca target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" href=\"https://www.1stdibs.com/creators/cesare-casati/furniture/\"\u003ECesare Casati\u003c/a\u003E and \u003ca target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" href=\"https://www.1stdibs.com/creators/ennio-lucini/furniture/\"\u003EEnnio Lucini\u003c/a\u003E.\u003c/p\u003E\n\u003cp\u003EFrom 1967 to 1968, Harvey Guzzini also participated in “Domus: Formes Italiennes,” an exhibition held at the \u003ca target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" href=\"https://haussmann.galerieslafayette.com/en/galeries-lafayette-the-best-shopping-mall-in-paris/\"\u003EGaleries Lafayette\u003c/a\u003E in Paris. By 1969, the company had grown into one of the best-known design firms in the country and opened a retail outlet in central Milan. Famous Harvey Guzzini designs include Massoni and Luciano Buttura's \u003ca target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" href=\"https://www.1stdibs.com/buy/guzzini-mushroom-lamp/\"\u003EMushroom table lamp\u003c/a\u003E (1965) as well as the in-house designed \u003ca target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" href=\"https://www.1stdibs.com/buy/guzzini-arc-floor-lamp/\"\u003EArc floor lamp\u003c/a\u003E (1968), \u003ca target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" href=\"https://www.1stdibs.com/buy/guzzini-faro/\"\u003EFaro table lamp\u003c/a\u003E (1970) and Toledo table lamp (1973).&nbsp;\u003c/p\u003E\n\u003cp\u003EIn 1974, Harvey Guzzini rebranded as iGuzzini. The company introduced a range of new and technically advanced lighting fixtures, including low-voltage halogen lamps. In 1977, iGuzzini organized the first Italian lighting design conference. In 1991, it was awarded the \u003ca target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" href=\"https://www.adidesignmuseum.org/en/il-premio-compasso-doro/\"\u003ECompasso d'Oro\u003c/a\u003E for its commitment to design.\u003c/p\u003E\n\u003cp\u003EToday, iGuzzini remains headquartered in Recanati and is a leading international architectural lighting group with a rich heritage spanning more than six decades since its early days as Harvey Guzzini. fill-rule="evenodd"></path></svg></div><span></span></div><h2 id="ot-pc-title">Privacy Preferences</h2><div id="ot-pc-desc">When you visit any website, it may store or retrieve information on your browser, mostly in the form of cookies. This information might be about you, your preferences or your device and is mostly used to make the site work as you expect it to. The information does not usually directly identify you, but it can give you a more personalized web experience. Because we respect your right to privacy, you can choose not to allow some types of cookies. Click on the different category headings to find out more and change our default settings. However, blocking some types of cookies may impact your experience of the site and the services we are able to offer.
            <br><a href="https://cookiepedia.co.uk/giving-consent-to-cookies" class="privacy-notice-link" rel="noopener" target="_blank" aria-label="More information about your privacy, opens in a new tab">More information</a></div><button id="accept-recommended-btn-handler" ot-button-order="0">Allow All Cookies</button><section class="ot-sdk-row ot-cat-grp"><h3 id="ot-category-title">Manage Cookies</h3><div class="ot-accordion-layout ot-cat-item ot-vs-config" data-optanongroupid="C0001"><button aria-expanded="false" ot-accordion="true" aria-controls="ot-desc-id-C0001" aria-labelledby="ot-header-id-C0001 ot-status-id-C0001"></button><!-- Accordion header --><div class="ot-acc-hdr ot-always-active-group"><div class="ot-plus-minus"><span></span><span></span></div><h4 class="ot-cat-header" id="ot-header-id-C0001">Strictly Necessary Cookies</h4><div id="ot-status-id-C0001" class="ot-always-active">Always Active</div></div><!-- accordion detail --><div class="ot-acc-grpcntr ot-acc-txt"><p class="ot-acc-grpdesc ot-category-desc" id="ot-desc-id-C0001">These cookies are necessary for the website to function and cannot be switched off in our systems. They are usually only set in response to actions made by you which amount to a request for services, such as setting your privacy preferences, logging in or filling in forms. You can set your browser to block or alert you about these cookies, but some parts of the site will not then work. These cookies do not store any personally identifiable information.</p><div class="ot-hlst-cntr"><button class="ot-link-btn category-host-list-handler" aria-label="Strictly Necessary Cookies - Cookie Details button opens Cookie List menu" data-parent-id="C0001">View Cookies Details&lrm;</button></div></div></div><div class="ot-accordion-layout ot-cat-item ot-vs-config" data-optanongroupid="C0003"><button aria-expanded="false" ot-accordion="true" aria-controls="ot-desc-id-C0003" aria-labelledby="ot-header-id-C0003"></button><!-- Accordion header --><div class="ot-acc-hdr"><div class="ot-plus-minus"><span></span><span></span></div><h4 class="ot-cat-header" id="ot-header-id-C0003">Functional Cookies</h4><div class="ot-tgl"><input type="checkbox" name="ot-group-id-C0003" id="ot-group-id-C0003" role="switch" class="category-switch-handler" data-optanongroupid="C0003" checked="" aria-labelledby="ot-header-id-C0003"> <label class="ot-switch" for="ot-group-id-C0003"><span class="ot-switch-nob"></span> <span class="ot-label-txt">Functional Cookies</span></label> </div></div><!-- accordion detail --><div class="ot-acc-grpcntr ot-acc-txt"><p class="ot-acc-grpdesc ot-category-desc" id="ot-desc-id-C0003">These cookies enable the website to provide enhanced functionality and personalisation. They may be set by us or by third party providers whose services we have added to our pages. If you do not allow these cookies then some or all of these services may not function properly.</p><div class="ot-hlst-cntr"><button class="ot-link-btn category-host-list-handler" aria-label="Functional Cookies - Cookie Details button opens Cookie List menu" data-parent-id="C0003">View Cookies Details&lrm;</button></div></div></div><div class="ot-accordion-layout ot-cat-item ot-vs-config" data-optanongroupid="C0002"><button aria-expanded="false" ot-accordion="true" aria-controls="ot-desc-id-C0002" aria-labelledby="ot-header-id-C0002"></button><!-- Accordion header --><div class="ot-acc-hdr"><div class="ot-plus-minus"><span></span><span></span></div><h4 class="ot-cat-header" id="ot-header-id-C0002">Performance Cookies</h4><div class="ot-tgl"><input type="checkbox" name="ot-group-id-C0002" id="ot-group-id-C0002" role="switch" class="category-switch-handler" data-optanongroupid="C0002" checked="" aria-labelledby="ot-header-id-C0002"> <label class="ot-switch" for="ot-group-id-C0002"><span class="ot-switch-nob"></span> <span class="ot-label-txt">Performance Cookies</span></label> </div></div><!-- accordion detail --><div class="ot-acc-grpcntr ot-acc-txt"><p class="ot-acc-grpdesc ot-category-desc" id="ot-desc-id-C0002">These cookies allow us to count visits and traffic sources so we can measure and improve the performance of our site. They help us to know which pages are the most and least popular and see how visitors move around the site. All information these cookies collect is aggregated and therefore anonymous.
